Wow Dave--

I have an awfully hard time believing that the finish on any wheel would
start flowing--
That's really crazy--

Think about all the litigation that would be going on if this was a
fact,
There would be wheels flying off all kinds of vehicles--the roads would
be lined with them--

I ain't buying that one--
And I do agree with you--them wheels never get that hot---

Maybe if you had a stuck caliper riding on the rotor all day--maybe it
would make the wheel awfully hot--but not enough to make any powder
coating run---

Have you ever seen any paint on any wheel blister from brake heat?

I sure haven't--and powder coating is tougher than paint--

More key board thinking from Jamie (?)--:>)_

See Ya--

