Terry,
Whooo! Jamie Rivers(I think) and I had this conversation about a year
ago and his experience was close to personal. He blamed it on the fact
that the drum/rotor got very hot and caused the powder coat to flow
again.
I listened and paid attention and when I recently did some wheels in
powder coat, it didn't bother me at all...because! I have had to reheat
some already powder coated stuff and realized two things....it really
doesn't "flow" again except at about 400 degrees plus(and not even
really then). The second part was that I have a infrared thermometer now
and have checked my drums/ brakes after several hi speed stops...
The *rims*/lug nut parts never got anywhere close to that temperature...
So, I torqued mine down good and drove off into the sunset....
Cheers, dave
